org.pikater.core.agents.system

Class Agent_DataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • jade.core.Agent
      • org.pikater.core.agents.PikaterAgent
        • org.pikater.core.agents.system.Agent_DataManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    jade.core.TimerListener, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Runnable

    public class Agent_DataManager
extends PikaterAgent

    This agent implementation is used to commit database changes made from the core system and also provides database entities to other agents.

    Each method corresponds to a particular use case.

    Author:
    siposp

      • respondToSaveAgentInfo

        protected jade.lang.acl.ACLMessage respondToSaveAgentInfo(jade.lang.acl.ACLMessage request,
                                              jade.content.onto.basic.Action action)
        Attempts to save an instance of AgentInfo wrapped in SaveAgentInfo to database and responds with the result:
        • If there is no record about the agent (class name) in database yet, the object is stored successfully.
        • If such record already exists, FAILURE message is returned.
        Parameters:
        request - ACLMessage received with the request.
        action - Action providing the AgentInfo object wrapped in SaveAgentInfo.
        Returns:
        see above

      • respondToUpdateBatchStatus

        protected jade.lang.acl.ACLMessage respondToUpdateBatchStatus(jade.lang.acl.ACLMessage request,
                                                  jade.content.onto.basic.Action action)

        Updates the given batch's status with the given status. Both of them are specified by UpdateBatchStatus object wrapped within the action.

        As a side effect:
        • If the given status is JPABatchStatus.COMPUTING, sets the start time for the given batch.
        • If the given status is JPABatchStatus.FAILED or JPABatchStatus.FINISHED, sets the finish time for the given batch.
        Parameters:
        request - ACLMessage received with the request.
        action - Action containing UpdateBatchStatus action.
        Returns:
        ACLMessage confirming the batch status update.

      • respondToUpdateExperimentStatus

        protected jade.lang.acl.ACLMessage respondToUpdateExperimentStatus(jade.lang.acl.ACLMessage request,
                                                       jade.content.onto.basic.Action action)
        Changes status of the given experiment to the given value, wrapped in UpdateExperimentStatus. As a side effect:
        • If the new status is COMPUTING, start time of the experiment is reset to now.
        • If the new status is FAILED or FINISHED, finish time of the experiment is reset to now.
        Parameters:
        request - ACLMessage of the request.
        action - Action containing the UpdateExperimentStatus
        Returns:
        ACLMessage of the reply
